'''Don Collins Reed''' (born in [[Fayetteville, Arkansas]]) is an emeritus [[professor]] of [[ethics]] and [[history of philosophy]] at [[Wittenberg University]].<ref name="wittenberg">[http://www5.wittenberg.edu/academics/phil/facultystaff/dreed.html Don Collins Reed, Ph.D. – Wittenberg University]</ref><ref name="liberia">[https://archive.is/20130414164528/http://christian-formation.diosohio.org/digital_faith/dfcfiles/1401271 Companion Relationship Discernment with the Episcopal Church of Liberia]</ref>

Reed's early research has focused on the work of the ethicist [[Lawrence Kohlberg]].  In ''[[Following Kohlberg: Liberalism and the Practice of Democratic Community]]'', published in 1998, Reed outlined the extension of principles of [[ethical community]], developed by Kohlberg and [[Carol Gilligan]], to that of [[deliberative democracy]].  Between 2003 and 2009, Reed observed and volunteered in [[State school|public school]] and [[preschool]] classrooms in [[Springfield, Ohio]], and served on the [[Board of Education]] of [[Springfield City School District|Springfield City Schools]].  His current research involves developing an integrated, multi-level model of human moral functioning based on recent [[science|scientific research]] on [[morality]].

